#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:957
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &plasmoid;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:959
#, no-c-format
msgid "&smb4k; comes with a &plasmoid; that can be added as a widget to the desktop or the panel. It consists of five tabs: <guilabel>Network Neighborhood</guilabel>, <guilabel>Mounted Shares</guilabel>, <guilabel>Bookmarks</guilabel>, <guilabel>Profiles</guilabel>, and <guilabel>Configuration</guilabel>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:962
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the plasmoid on the desktop"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:965
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the plasmoid"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:974
#, no-c-format
msgid "Network Neighborhood Tab"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:976
#, no-c-format
msgid "On the <guilabel>Network Neighborhood</guilabel> page the network items are arranged in a list view:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:979
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the plasmoid's network neighborhood tab"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:982 index.docbook:1004 index.docbook:1024
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bookmarks tab of the plasmoid"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:986
#, no-c-format
msgid "By clicking an entry you either enter the level below (&eg; clicking a workgroup or domain item will show a list of all hosts belonging to it), mount the selected share, or invoke the print dialog. To go one level up, you need to click the <guibutton>Up</guibutton> button in the tool bar."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:987
#, no-c-format
msgid "For hosts and shares, there are some action buttons to the right of the network item's name. For hosts, there is one button with which you can open the <link linkend=\"network_neighborhood_browser_defining_custom_settings\">Custom Settings</link> editor. For shares, there are additional buttons for <link linkend=\"network_neighborhood_browser_previewing\">previewing the content of the selected share</link> and for <link linkend=\"bookmarks_adding\">adding the share to the bookmarks</link>. The action buttons are transparent by default and change to opaque when you move the mouse over them. By left clicking, you initiate the chosen action."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:988
#, no-c-format
msgid "Besides the <guibutton>Up</guibutton> button, the tool bar contains three more entries: <guibutton>Rescan</guibutton>, <guibutton>Abort</guibutton> and <guibutton>Mount Dialog</guibutton>. With these you can do a rescan, abort any running action, or open the <link linkend=\"network_neighborhood_browser_mounting\">mount dialog</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:996
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mounted Shares Tab"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:998
#, no-c-format
msgid "On the <guilabel>Mounted Shares</guilabel> page all mounted shares are listed:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1001
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the plasmoid's mounted shares tab"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1007
#, no-c-format
msgid "At the right side of each entry, three action buttons are arranged. The first is for <link linkend=\"bookmarks_adding\">adding a bookmark</link>, the second is for <link linkend=\"shares_view_synchronization\">synchronization</link>, and the third is for <link linkend=\"shares_view_unmounting\">unmounting the share</link>. The action buttons are transparent by default and change to opaque when you move your mouse over them. By left clicking you initiate the selected action."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1008
#, no-c-format
msgid "The tool bar contains the <guibutton>Unmount All</guibutton> action that lets you unmount all your shares at once."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1016
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bookmarks Tab"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1018
#, no-c-format
msgid "The bookmarks are listed on the <guilabel>Bookmarks</guilabel> page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1021
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the plasmoid's bookmarks tab"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1028
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bookmarked shares can be mounted by left clicking the respective bookmark. To edit or remove the bookmarks, press the <guibutton>Edit</guibutton> action button in the tool bar to open the <link linkend=\"bookmarks_editor\">Bookmark Editor</link>. To get back to the top level from a category folder, use the <guibutton>Back</guibutton> button."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1036
#, no-c-format
msgid "Profiles Tab"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1038
#, no-c-format
msgid "All defined profiles are listed on the <guilabel>Profiles</guilabel> page. The currently active profile is marked with an appended <guilabel>(active)</guilabel> label."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1041
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the plasmoid's profiles tab"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1044
#, no-c-format
msgid "Profiles tab of the plasmoid"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1048
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can activate a certain profile by clicking it. All profiles can be <link linkend=\"profiles\">managed</link> via the <link linkend=\"configuration_page_profiles\">configuration dialog</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1056
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuration Tab"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1058
#, no-c-format
msgid "To configure the behavior of &smb4k;, you can launch the <link linkend=\"configuration\">configuration dialog</link> on the <guilabel>Configuration</guilabel> page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1061
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the plasmoid's configuration tab"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1064
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuration tab of the plasmoid"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1069
#, no-c-format
msgid "You should not open two configuration dialogs (through the main application and via the &plasmoid;) at the same time, because they might interfere with each other."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1080 index.docbook:4066
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bookmarks"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1089
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can add bookmarks to your favorite shares from within the <link linkend=\"network_neighborhood_browser\">network neighborhood browser</link>, the <link linkend=\"shares_view\">shares view</link> and the <link linkend=\"plasmoid\">&plasmoid;</link>. In the main window, this is done by selecting one or more shares and clicking the <menuchoice><guimenuitem>Add Bookmark</guimenuitem></menuchoice> action. In the &plasmoid;, you click the respective bookmark action next to the item's name. The <guilabel>Bookmark Shares</guilabel> dialog will pop up, listing all shares that are to be newly bookmarked."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1091
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the bookmarks addition dialog"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1094
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bookmarks addition dialog"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1097
#, no-c-format
msgid "To add a label or assign a category, double-click a bookmark. The input widget will open and you can edit the corresponding entries."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1099
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the bookmarks addition dialog with opened input widget"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1102
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bookmarks addition dialog with opened input widget"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1105
#, no-c-format
msgid "Defining categories may help you organize the bookmarks. In the <link linkend=\"bookmarks_menu\">bookmark menu</link>, all bookmarks belonging to the same category are arranged in a respective submenu."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1106
#, no-c-format
msgid "The label can be any text describing the share. In case you define a label, it will be displayed in the bookmarks menu instead of the location by default. If you want to change this behavior, you can do so in the <link linkend=\"configuration_page_user_interface_main_window\">configuration dialog</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1114
#, no-c-format
msgid "Accessing and Managing Bookmarks"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1116
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the main window, the bookmarks can be accessed and managed through the <guilabel>Bookmarks</guilabel> menu."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1119
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the bookmark popup menu"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1122
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bookmark popup menu"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1126
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are two static items in the menu:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1131
#, no-c-format
msgid "Edit Bookmarks"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1134
#, no-c-format
msgid "Opens the <link linkend=\"bookmarks_editor\">bookmark editor</link>. This entry is disabled if there are no bookmarks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1145
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adds bookmarks to the selected shares. At least one share must be selected to enable this entry."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1150
#, no-c-format
msgid "If there are bookmarks present that are not assigned to a category, and are, thus, shown directly at the top level of the menu, a third item is present:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1155
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mount Bookmarks"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1158
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mount all top level bookmarks at once. This entry is disabled if all bookmarked shares are already mounted."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1163
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following entries are category submenus and bookmarks that do not belong to any category. The entries are listed alphabetically and the bookmarks may appear either with their location or a descriptive label. If you click a bookmark, the respective share will be mounted. In case a bookmarked share is already mounted, the entry is disabled."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1164
#, no-c-format
msgid "The category submenus contain the assigned bookmarks as well as a <guimenuitem>Mount Bookmarks</guimenuitem> menu item. It can be used to mount all bookmarks in that category at once."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1165
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the system tray widget, there is a similar <guilabel>Bookmarks</guilabel> <link linkend=\"systemtray_menus\">submenu</link> which, however, does not come with the <guilabel>Add Bookmark</guilabel> entry."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1166
#, no-c-format
msgid "The &plasmoid; provides a <guilabel>Bookmarks</guilabel> <link linkend=\"plasmoid_bookmarks\">tab</link> where all bookmarks are arranged in a similar manner as in the bookmark menu. For further details read <link linkend=\"plasmoid_bookmarks\">this section</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1174
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editing Bookmarks"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1176
#, no-c-format
msgid "The bookmarks may be edited or removed via the bookmark editor or the <guilabel>Bookmarks</guilabel> page in the <link linkend=\"configuration_page_bookmarks\">configuration dialog</link>. The bookmark editor can be opened by clicking the <guimenuitem>Edit Bookmarks</guimenuitem> entry in the <guilabel>Bookmarks</guilabel> menu or the <guimenuitem>Edit</guimenuitem> action in the <guilabel>Bookmarks</guilabel> tab of the &plasmoid;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1178
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the bookmark editor"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1181
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bookmark editor"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1184
#, no-c-format
msgid "In the tree view, the bookmarks are arranged according to the categories they belong to. Bookmarks without a category are located at the top level. To rearrange bookmarks, the tree view offers drag and drop capabilities, so you can move bookmarks around with the mouse."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1185
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you want to edit a bookmark, you can do so by either double-clicking or selecting it and pressing the <guibutton>Edit</guibutton>button. The input widget will then be shown. Here you can edit the label, category name, login, workgroup or domain name and the IP address."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1187
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the bookmark editor with opened input widget"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1190
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bookmark editor with opened input widget"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1193
#, no-c-format
msgid "In most cases, you do not need to touch the IP address and the login, because &smb4k; stores the correct values at the time you bookmark the share. However, if the server got a different IP address (&eg; because DHCP is used on your local network), or your login changed, these entries should be adjusted. You also should adjust the workgroup or domain name, if its name was discovered by DNS-SD (and is most likely called <emphasis>LOCAL</emphasis>). With the label you can give each bookmark a custom description. It will be used for display <emphasis>instead</emphasis> of the location, but this can be changed in the <link linkend=\"configuration_page_user_interface_main_window\">configuration dialog</link>. Finally,the category entry helps you to organize your bookmarks. For instance, if you use your notebook at home and also at work, and you do not want to use <link linkend=\"profiles\">profiles</link>, it might be a good idea to create two categories, \"Home\" and \"Work\", and categorize the bookmarks accordingly."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1194
#, no-c-format
msgid "With the <guibutton>Add Category</guibutton> button, you can add a category. The <guibutton>Remove</guibutton> button removes the selected bookmark and the <guibutton>Clear List</guibutton> button clears the whole list of bookmarks. As long as you have not saved the changes by clicking the <guibutton>Save</guibutton> button, you can reset all your changes with the <guibutton>Reset</guibutton> button."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1203 index.docbook:4098
#, no-c-format
msgid "Custom Settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1206
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using Custom Settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1208
#, no-c-format
msgid "Besides the global settings that can be defined in the <link linkend=\"configuration\">configuration dialog</link>, &smb4k; offers the possibility to configure individual settings per server or share. You can make use of these custom settings if you want to"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1210
#, no-c-format
msgid "define individual browse or mount settings for a single server or share that deviate from the values defined in the configuration dialog,"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1211
#, no-c-format
msgid "define a server that should be awakened prior to network scans or mount attempts (Wake-On-LAN feature, see <link linkend=\"configuration_page_network_advanced_settings_wake_on_lan\">here</link>),"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1212
#, no-c-format
msgid "always mount a particular share on start-up or when the corresponding profile is loaded."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1217
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding Custom Settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1219
#, no-c-format
msgid "To define custom settings, in both, the <link linkend=\"network_neighborhood_browser_actions_popup_menu\">network neighborhood browser</link> and the <link linkend=\"shares_view_actions_popup_menu\">shares view</link>, you can open the editor for the custom settings by clicking the <menuchoice><shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl; <keycap>C</keycap></keycombo></shortcut><guimenuitem>Add Custom Settings</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu entry."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1222
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the custom settings editor for a share"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1228
#, no-c-format
msgid "The custom settings editor"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1233
#, no-c-format
msgid "Custom settings that you defined for a server will also be applied to its shares."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1235
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following settings can be made:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1240
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Basic Settings</guilabel>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1243
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can set the IP address and the workgroup or domain of the server here. If you selected a share, you can also check the <guibutton>Always remount this share</guibutton> button to remount it every time you start &smb4k; or load the respective <link linkend=\"profiles\">profile</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1247
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Common Mount Settings</guilabel> (&Linux; only)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1251
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can define common settings related to mounting here. For detailed information about these settings have a look at <link linkend=\"configuration_page_mounting_common_mount_settings\">this section</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1255
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Advanced Mount Settings</guilabel> (&Linux; only)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1259
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can define advanced settings related to mounting here. For detailed information about these settings have a look at <link linkend=\"configuration_page_mounting_advanced_mount_settings\">this section</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1263
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Mount Settings</guilabel> (BSD only)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1267
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can define settings related to mounting here. For detailed information about these settings have a look at <link linkend=\"configuration_page_mounting_mount_settings\">this section</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1272
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guilabel>Browse Settings</guilabel>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1275
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can define the minimal and maximal SMB protocol versions as well as the SMB port to be used. In addition, you can decide if Kerberos should be used for authentication. For detailed information about these settings have a look at <link linkend=\"configuration_page_network\">this section</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guilabel
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1280
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wake-On-LAN Settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1283
#, no-c-format
msgid "To make the Wake-On-LAN feature work, you must provide the MAC address of the server you selected. Currently, &smb4k; has no way to determine the MAC address, so you need to find it on your own. Afterwards, you can define if the server should be woken up by sending a magic Wake-On-LAN packet before the network neighborhood is scanned and/or one of its shares is mounted."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1284
#, no-c-format
msgid "Please note that you need to enable the Wake-On-LAN capabilities in the <link linkend=\"configuration_page_network_advanced_settings_wake_on_lan\">configuration dialog</link> to take advantage of these settings."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1289
#, no-c-format
msgid "With the <guibutton>Defaults</guibutton> button you can reset all settings in the editor to their default values as they are defined in the configuration dialog. Custom settings that only contain default values are removed. Using the <guibutton>Reset</guibutton> button, you can reset the entries in the dialog to their initial values. Clicking the <guibutton>Save</guibutton> button saves the custom settings and closes the dialog."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1290
#, no-c-format
msgid "Please note that under BSD the dialog contains fewer entries than if you run &Linux;, because several of the options are not supported."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1294
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editing Custom Settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1296
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can edit or reset the settings of individual network items by opening the custom settings editor. A complete overview of all custom settings provides the <link linkend=\"configuration_page_custom_settings\"><guilabel>Custom Settings</guilabel> configuration page</link>, where you also can edit or remove the desired settings."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1305 index.docbook:4129 index.docbook:4166
#, no-c-format
msgid "Profiles"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1307
#, no-c-format
msgid "&smb4k; offers the option to use different profiles. They are intended to facilitate handling of different network neighborhoods, &eg;, if you are using your laptop at home and also at work."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1308
#, no-c-format
msgid "By default, the use of profiles is disabled. Most users won't have to change this, because the default behavior satisfies their needs completely. However, for some users this feature might be useful."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1315
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling and Managing Profiles"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1316
#, no-c-format
msgid "The use of different profiles can be enabled in the <link linkend=\"configuration_page_profiles\">configuration dialog</link> by ticking the <guibutton>Use profiles</guibutton> checkbox. The initial active profile is then set and indicated by the tick mark next to it in the list view. The name of the active profile is also shown in parentheses in the title of the <guilabel>Authentication</guilabel>, <guilabel>Bookmarks</guilabel> and <guilabel>Custom Settings</guilabel> configuration pages."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1318
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Screenshot of the title section of the Authentication configuration page with indicated profile</screeninfo>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1324
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Screenshot of the title section of the Authentication configuration page with indicated profile</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1329
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are two pre-defined profiles, <guilabel>Home</guilabel> and <guilabel>Work</guilabel>, but you can have as many profiles as you want. A new profile is added by entering its name into the input line and then clicking the <guibutton>Add</guibutton> button."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1331
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the Profiles configuration page (add profile)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1337
#, no-c-format
msgid "Profiles configuration page (add profile)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1341
#, no-c-format
msgid "To set the active profile, either double click the profile name or mark the profile name and click the <guibutton>Set Active</guibutton> button. To rename a profile, select it, click <guibutton>Rename</guibutton> and edit the name in the list view. All custom settings, bookmarks and default login credentials will be migrated seamlessly to the new name. To remove a profile, select it and click <guibutton>Remove</guibutton>. You may also change the order of the profiles with the <guibutton>Move Up</guibutton> and <guibutton>Move Down</guibutton> buttons."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1349
#, no-c-format
msgid "Activating a Profile"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1351
#, no-c-format
msgid "The active profile can either be changed in the configuration dialog as mentioned <link linkend=\"profiles_enable\">above</link>, or in the <guimenu>Profiles</guimenu> menu of the main window or system tray widget, or on the <guilabel>Profiles</guilabel> page of the plasmoid."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1352
#, no-c-format
msgid "When a profile is activated, these things happen:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1354
#, no-c-format
msgid "All currently mounted shares are unmounted and scheduled for remount."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1355
#, no-c-format
msgid "All shares that were previously mounted under the newly activated profile are remounted."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1356
#, no-c-format
msgid "The default login credentials (if defined), bookmarks and custom settings from the new profile are loaded."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1358
#, no-c-format
msgid "So, don't be surprised when things change after you select a different profile ..."
msgstr ""

