#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1409
#, no-c-format
msgid "Trouble Shooting"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1416
#, no-c-format
msgid "Missing Programs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1418
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the system is missing some of the programs &smb4k; needs to operate properly, it notifies the user:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1421
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the missing program notification"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1424
#, no-c-format
msgid "The missing program notification"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1428
#, no-c-format
msgid "In this case, please install the specified program or, if it is already present, add its location to the <envar>PATH</envar> environment variable in your shell's configuration file (for the <ulink url=\"man:/bash\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>bash</refentrytitle><manvolnum>1</manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> shell it is the <filename>~/.bashrc</filename> file)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1436
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zeroconf Error"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1438
#, no-c-format
msgid "&smb4k; uses the Zeroconf service (<application><ulink url=\"https://avahi.org\">Avahi</ulink></application>) to look up servers and shares in the network neighborhood using DNS Service Discovery (DNS-SD). For this to work, the Avahi daemon must be enabled and running on your system. If this is not the case, &smb4k; shows an error message:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screeninfo
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1441
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the Zeroconf error notification"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1444
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Zeroconf error notification"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1448
#, no-c-format
msgid "In most cases, the Avahi daemon is not running when an error is reported. Under those &Linux; distributions that use <application>systemd</application> you can start it by running the following or a similar command from the terminal:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1449
#, no-c-format
msgid "<userinput><prompt>$</prompt> <command>sudo</command> <command>systemctl</command> enable --now avahi-daemon</userinput>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1450
#, no-c-format
msgid "With all other &Linux; distributions and under BSD refer to the specific documentation how to start the Avahi daemon."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1458
#, no-c-format
msgid "Denied Privilege Escalation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1460
#, no-c-format
msgid "In case the mount and unmount actions fail (most likely with an <guilabel>AuthorizationDeniedError</guilabel> message), your polkit-1 setup might need to be adjusted: Add a file, &eg; named <filename>10-mounthelper.rules</filename>, to the <filename class=\"directory\">$PREFIX/etc/polkit-1/rules.d/</filename> directory with the following content:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1462
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"polkit.addRule(function(action, subject) {\n"
"        if (action.id == \"org.kde.smb4k.mounthelper.mount\" &amp;&amp; \n"
"            subject.isInGroup(\"wheel\")) {\n"
"                return polkit.Result.YES;\n"
"        }\n"
"});\n"
"\n"
"polkit.addRule(function(action, subject) {\n"
"        if (action.id == \"org.kde.smb4k.mounthelper.unmount\" &amp;&amp;\n"
"            subject.isInGroup(\"wheel\")) {\n"
"                return polkit.Result.YES;\n"
"        }\n"
"});"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1464
#, no-c-format
msgid "This allows all users in the Unix group <emphasis>wheel</emphasis> to execute the mount and unmount actions. You may adjust the group of authorized users to any group you prefer to use (&eg; <emphasis>sudo</emphasis> or <emphasis>operator</emphasis>)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1472
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mounting Problems Under BSD"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1474
#, no-c-format
msgid "If mounting of shares from either a &Samba; or a &Windows; server fails, this might be because <ulink url=\"man:/mount_smbfs\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount_smbfs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> only uses NTLMv1 authentication and requires the SMB 1.0/&CIFS; protocol, and the server does not support those. To fix mounting for a &Samba; server, you can add the following entries to the [global] section of the <ulink url=\"man:/smb.conf\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle><filename>smb.conf</filename></refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> file of <emphasis>the server</emphasis>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1476
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"[global]\n"
"...\n"
"ntlm auth = yes\n"
"server min protocol = NT1\n"
"..."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1478
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you want to fix this issue for a &Windows; server, please contact the sysadmin and tell her or him that NTLMv1 authentication and the SMB 1.0/&CIFS; protocol should be switched on (if possible)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1480
#, no-c-format
msgid "It is not advisable to enable the SMB 1.0/&CIFS; protocol on a server, because it is considered insecure (see &eg; <ulink url=\"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/storage-at-microsoft/stop-using-smb1/ba-p/425858\">here</ulink>) and was thus disabled in newer &Samba; and &Windows; versions (see &eg; <ulink url=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/archive/blogs/josebda/the-deprecation-of-smb1-you-should-be-planning-to-get-rid-of-this-old-smb-dialect\">here</ulink> and <ulink url=\"https://www.samba.org/samba/history/samba-4.11.0.html\">here</ulink>)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1488
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other Desktop Environments Than &plasma;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1490
#, no-c-format
msgid "When using a different desktop environment than &plasma;, &Qt; and &kde-frameworks; applications might be missing some icons. In that case, you might want to install the <application>qt6ct</application> (<ulink url=\"https://github.com/trialuser02/qt6ct\">download</ulink>) application. To use it with your desktop environment, add the following to your <filename>~/.xinitrc</filename> or <filename>~/.profile</filename> file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1491
#, no-c-format
msgid "X11:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1492
#, no-c-format
msgid "export QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME=qt6ct"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: emphasis
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1493
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wayland:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1494
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"export QT_QPA_PLATFORM=wayland\n"
"export QT_QPA_PLATFORMTHEME=qt6ct"
msgstr ""

