#. Tag: title
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1744
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Browse Settings</title>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guibutton
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1749
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use Web Services Dynamic Discovery (WS-Discovery) for browsing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1752
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Web Services Dynamic Discovery (WS-Discovery) protocol is used to browse the local network and discover workgroups, domains and hosts. This is useful if your network neighborhood is dominated by servers with modern &Windows; versions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1753
#, no-c-format
msgid "This setting is optional, and only appears if you compiled &smb4k; with WS-Discovery support."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guibutton
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1759
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use DNS Service Discovery (DNS-SD) for browsing"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1762
#, no-c-format
msgid "The DNS Service Discovery (DNS-SD) interface is used to browse the local network and discover servers that provide shared SMB resources. The discovered domains correspond to the local DNS domains (&eg; named LOCAL) and most likely not the ones defined in the network neighborhood. However, this does not influence the browsing."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guibutton
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1768
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set minimal and maximal SMB protocol version"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1771
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set the minimal and maximal SMB protocol version that is used by &Samba;'s client library to browse the network neighborhood. This will override the settings in the smb.conf file. Normally, you do not need to use this option, because the right protocol versions should be negotiated between the client and the server while establishing a connection. Please note that this setting might not be appropriate to make the discovery of workgroups and domains work while keeping undisturbed connectivity to servers. Use DNS Service Discovery (DNS-SD) or Web Services Dynamic Discovery (WS-Discovery) for domain and workgroup lookups instead."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1772
#, no-c-format
msgid "The settings below for the minimal and maximal SMB protocol version are enabled by checking this checkbox."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: index.docbook:1773
#, no-c-format
msgid "The maximal SMB protocol version must be equal to or greater than the minimal SMB protocol version."
msgstr ""

